# Flint — Rust Conventions

## Error Handling & Logging

- Use `anyhow::Result` for all fallible functions.
- Use `thiserror` for defining domain-specific error types.
- Use `tracing` (not `println!`, not `log`) for all logging.
- All log lines include `session_id` when inside a session context.
- Every `tokio::spawn` task has a named span: `tracing::info_span!("thread_name")`.
- `DEBUG` logs compiled out in release (`#[cfg(debug_assertions)]`).
- NEVER show raw Rust errors to users — map all errors to user-facing messages.

```rust
tracing::info!(
    session_id = %session_id,
    event = "directional_thread_complete",
    ttft_ms = ttft,
    provider = %provider_name,
    cache_hit = was_cache_hit,
    confidence = confidence_score,
    "directional thread finished"
);
```

## HTTP Calls
- Always set a timeout. One immediate retry. Then fallback. No silent hangs.
- 429 responses: honor `Retry-After` header. Queue under token-bucket limiter. Do NOT immediately failover on 429 — only on repeated budget breach.
- Rate limiter enforces 80% of documented provider free-tier limits.

## Failover Logic

```
Network failure (HTTP 5xx / timeout):
1. One immediate retry.
2. If retry fails: silent failover to Ollama → emit `failover_triggered`.
3. Background ping primary every 30 seconds.
4. On recovery: emit `primary_restored` → UI shows "Primary LLM restored. Switch back?"

429 rate limiting:
- Honor Retry-After. Queue under token-bucket. Do NOT failover on first 429.
- Only downgrade on repeated budget breach.
```

## Thread Safety
- Each `tokio::spawn` thread has its own error boundary (`catch_unwind` equivalent).
- One thread failing NEVER crashes other threads or the main process.

## Formatting & Lint
- `rustfmt` defaults. Enforce with `cargo fmt --check` in CI.
- `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` in CI. No clippy warnings in merged code.
- SQLite: always `PRAGMA journal_mode = WAL`. NEVER use DELETE mode.

## Service Interface Contracts

All external dependencies are behind traits in `interfaces/`. Implementations swap without touching orchestrator or core logic.

```rust
#[async_trait]
trait AuthInterface: Send + Sync {
    async fn signup(&self, email: &str, password: &str) -> Result<User>;
    async fn login(&self, email: &str, password: &str) -> Result<AuthToken>;
    async fn logout(&self, token: &AuthToken) -> Result<()>;
    async fn refresh(&self, refresh_token: &SecretString) -> Result<AuthToken>;
    async fn get_current_user(&self, token: &AuthToken) -> Result<User>;
    async fn delete_account(&self, token: &AuthToken) -> Result<()>;
}

#[async_trait]
trait SessionInterface: Send + Sync {
    async fn create(&self, token: &AuthToken, config: SessionConfig) -> Result<Session>;
    async fn get(&self, token: &AuthToken, session_id: Uuid) -> Result<Session>;
    async fn list(&self, token: &AuthToken) -> Result<Vec<SessionSummary>>;
    async fn save(&self, token: &AuthToken, data: SessionData) -> Result<()>;
    async fn promote(&self, token: &AuthToken, session_id: Uuid) -> Result<()>;
    async fn delete(&self, token: &AuthToken, session_id: Uuid) -> Result<()>;
}

#[async_trait]
trait VectorInterface: Send + Sync {
    async fn ingest(&self, session_id: Uuid, chunks: Vec<Chunk>) -> Result<()>;
    async fn query(&self, session_id: Uuid, embedding: &Embedding, top_k: usize) -> Result<Vec<ScoredChunk>>;
    async fn delete_session(&self, session_id: Uuid) -> Result<()>;
    fn chunk_count(&self, session_id: Uuid) -> usize;
}

#[async_trait]
trait LLMProvider: Send + Sync {
    async fn complete_stream(
        &self,
        prompt: String,
        config: CompletionConfig,
    ) -> Result<Pin<Box<dyn Stream<Item = Result<String>> + Send>>>;
    fn name(&self) -> &str;
    fn is_available(&self) -> bool;
    fn context_window(&self) -> usize;
    fn rate_limit(&self) -> RateLimit;
}
```

## Feature Flags Evaluation

```rust
fn is_enabled(flag: &str, user: &User) -> bool {
    let flag_config = get_flag(flag);
    if !flag_config.enabled { return false; }
    if !flag_config.allowed_plans.contains(&user.plan) { return false; }
    let hash = stable_hash(&user.id) % 100;
    hash < flag_config.rollout_percentage
}
```

Kill switch: If Supabase unreachable at start, use locally cached flags (24h cache). If no cache: GA features enabled, unreleased features disabled.
